<TEXT>
shining path guerrillas killed 16 people 
in attacks on three nearby villages tuesday on the eve of the 
maoist movements ninth anniversary officials reported 
police said about 40 guerrillas with rifles revolvers and 
explosives burst into the hamlet of vinchos about five miles west 
of ayacucho early tuesday 
survivors of the attack told police that the guerrillas gathered 
the townspeople together and accused 14 of them of belonging to a 
peasant patrol before shooting them to death 
the governmentsupported patrols are organized in isolated 
regions to help peasants protect themselves from the shining path 
following the killings the guerrillas raided several homes 
taking with them clothes kerosene lamps and food police reported 
they then burned the homes police said 
in another incident guerrillas in the town of huanta 30 miles 
north of ayacucho killed an 18yearold man and left behind a sign 
reading this is how the traitors and snitches die police said 
officials said the man likely had collaborated with authorities 
in the past 
in a third attack on tuesday a peasant patrol leader in the 
village of runguyo just south of ayacucho was slain by 
guerrillas police said 
the shining path began near the andean city of ayacucho 235 
miles southeast of lima it began attacks on may 17 1980 in the 
town of chuschi about 30 miles southeast of ayacucho 
more than 14000 people including guerrillas peasants 
political authorities police and soldiers have been killed in the 
insurgency 
