<TEXT>
space shuttle atlantis is finally 
back at its launch site after a weatherinterrupted 2day odyssey 
across the south atop a nasa boeing 747 jetliner 
the jumbo jet landed here shortly before dark monday evening 
after making two unscheduled stops in texas and one in georgia on a 
trip from california that normally takes only a few hours 
atlantis and its five astronauts landed at edwards air force 
base calif on may 8 at the end of a fourday space mission that 
dispatched the magellan spacecraft on a 15month journey to venus 
to map the planet 
bolted atop the 747 the space shuttle left edwards on saturday 
but storms over central texas forced the 747 to stop at biggs army 
air field near el paso it sat on the ground there saturday and 
sunday nights waiting for the weather to clear 
the jet took off monday morning and landed at dallasfort worth 
international airport waiting for a few hours while forecasters 
assessed the weather between texas and florida 
with a threat of thunderstorms in central florida nasa decided 
to fly the 747 into warner robbins air force base near macon ga 
and again look at the weather 
officials had just about decided to stay overnight in georgia 
and complete the trip today when the florida clouds started to 
clear 
nasa sent a t38 jet out to survey the flight path and when the 
pilot gave the allclear the 747 took off on the final hourlong 
flight leg 
the darkening sky was clear here when the big jet and its 12 
billion shuttle passenger landed at 809 pm on a 15000foot 
runway just three miles from the launch pad where atlantis blasted 
into space on may 4 
the delayed trip could make the national aeronautics and space 
administration think about hastening the day when shuttles will end 
their space trips on the runway here all landings have been in 
california since a shuttle blew a tire here in april 1985 
officials have said they will continue to return orbiting shuttles 
to wideopen and safer edwards until new brake and steering systems 
have been throughly tested 
atlantis now will be readied for another planetary mission to 
propel the galileo spacecraft toward jupiter in october 
</TEXT>
