ogilvy group inc has agreed to an 864 million 
buyout offer in a deal that will create the worlds secondlargest 
advertising and marketing concern 
the boards of oglivy and wpp group plc announced early today 
they had approved the buyout under which the londonbased wpp will 
pay 54 a share in cash for all of ogilvys common stock 
the agreement came just hours before todays annual meeting of 
ogilvy shareholders 
while we would have preferred to remain independent and 
pursued many options to that end we became convinced that a 
combination with wpp represented the most attractive course for the 
future of our organization said ogilvys chairman kenneth roman 
but he said after intensive conversations he concluded the deal 
offered the best course for the company and its shareholders 
martin sorrell chief executive of wpp group said hes certain 
the combination will create the finest advertising and marketing 
services group in the world 
at a news conference this morning roman and sorrell said they 
would keep the ogilvy and thompson agencies autonomous roman said 
some ogilvy clients told him theyd like to discuss how the agency 
will be run under the wpp umbrella but none threatened to drop the 
agency as a result of the deal 
sorrell said he first thought about the possibility of acquiring 
ogilvy after meeting with roman in april 1988 but that it took 
nearly a year to decide to make a firm proposal 
sorrell began his pursuit of ogilvy only 2 weeks ago when he 
proposed a buyout at 45 a share 
roman said ogilvy preferred to remain independent and that its 
board would consider the offer in due course 
on may 8 wpp said it had proposed to pay 50 a share for ogilvy 
stock four days later ogilvy said it had entered into formal 
discussions with wpp after the latter indicated it would be willing 
to increase its offer from 50 a share in order to secure a 
friendly agreement 
the agreement would allow the new yorkbased ogilvy group to 
operate autonomously within wpp a fastgrowing conglomeration of 
advertising agencies public relations and marketing services 
concerns 
roman will continue to head the ogilvy operations within wpp 
in an added inducement wpp said it would appoint ogilvy founder 
david ogilvy chairman of wpp group the current wpp chairman john 
symonds will become deputy chairman 
only two years ago wpp stunned the advertising world with its 
uninvited but successful buyout of the parent of another us 
advertising giant j walter thompson that deal had cost 566 
million 
the combination of wpp and ogilvy will produce an advertising 
and marketing services giant that would have had combined billings 
in 1988 of about 135 billion 
that would put it only slightly behind the industry leader 
londonbased saatchi amp saatchi plc which had billings of just over 
135 billion in 1988 according to the trade magazine advertising 
age 
sorrell said he intended to pay for the acquisition by raising 
about 350 million through an issue of convertible preferred stock 
the rest would come from bank loans 
ogilvy founded in 1948 is one of the better known names in the 
advertising business its ogilvy amp mather ad agency has many 
bluechip clients including american express co american 
telephone amp telegraph co and sears roebuck and co 
