contracts are scheduled to begin this week 
the free press and the news are seeking permission from the us 
supreme court to combine some of their business functions 
editorial and news departments would remain separate 
the supreme court is expected to rule on the proposed joint 
operating agreement within a year 
the free press has promised its owner knightridder inc that 
it would hold losses to 1988 levels of more than 17 million while 
