<TEXT>
a helicopter filming an american 
action movie crashed and exploded today killing three americans 
and the filipino pilot and injuring up to 10 other people 
officials said 
two of the injured both american stuntmen were in critical 
condition doctors and members of the film crew said two other 
american stuntmen were seriously hurt but were not in 
lifethreatening condition doctors said 
police investigator jaime talay said the dolphin helicopter 
crashed at the foot of a hill near a mansion once owned by former 
president ferdinand marcos in tagaytay a mountain resort city 30 
miles south of manila 
talay said the helicopter was filming a scene for the movie 
delta force 2 starring american actor chuck norris when the 
accident occurred 
talay said the scene called for the helicopter to catch fire 
and it took several moments before the crew on the ground realized 
the crash was real 
a fire truck was stationed near the scene during the filming and 
helped extinguish the blaze talay said 
talay identified the three dead americans as don marshall mike 
graham and gaddi dansig marshall and graham were electricians and 
dansig was a cameraman according to members of the crew 
the filipino pilot jojo imperial died a few hours after the 
crash in a local hospital officials said 
a nurse at a hospital in nearby dasmarinas said up to 10 people 
were brought there with injuries but most were minor doctors at 
the hospital speaking on condition they not be named said two of 
the injured were in critical condition two others were seriously 
injured but were not in lifethreatening situations 
all four were american stuntmen crew members said 
one crew member who spoke on condition of anonymity said the 
helicopter had just taken off in preparation for taping a scene 
when it suddenly veered to the left and plunged into a 40foot 
ravine next to the former marcos mansion 
the accident was the second involving a norris film in the 
philippines 
in 1987 a philippine military sikorsky helicopter rented by 
norris crew crashed in manila bay killing three filipino soldiers 
who had been working as extras 
the 1987 crash took place while norris was filming missing in 
action part iii braddock 
