of military servicemen and us embassy workers already had 
departed panama on space available seats on military transports 
over the last few days 
but howard and other officials who asked not to be named said 
the defense department was now launching a much broader effort 
using chartered commercial planes in addition to the military cargo 
planes that have been ferrying extra troops to panama 
howard insisted several times at a briefing the movement of 
military dependents was not an evacuation but rather an 
accelerated drawdown 
the word evacuation suggests a nearpanic withdrawal and thats 
not what is happening now in panama howard said 
the spokesman said he didnt know how frequently flights would 
operate and to which cities in the united states they would run 
but a spokesman at the charleston sc air force base said today 
that at least some flights would be using that city as a point of 
entry 
lt lester t carroll jr the spokesman said the first of at 
least two evacuation flights of dependants from panama was 
scheduled for arrival in charleston tonight carrying between 200 
and 300 people 
there are about 14000 dependents of service personnel and 
defense department employees living in panama 
according to howard the pentagon and the us southern command 
which is headquartered in panama have decided that all socalled 
commandsponsored dependents will either be living inside us 
bases or transported home by july 1 
the pentagon announced monday that that all command 
sponsored military families those who are there under official 
us government sponsorship had moved inside us military bases 
in panama under an emergency order 
but there are not enough houses on the bases for those who had 
been living off base about 1396 people to stay there 
permanently howard said so while the evacuation flights are 
currently voluntary some dependents may face orders to fly home if 
not enough volunteer the spokesman said 
of the roughly 14000 military dependents in panama 3081 live 
off base of that total 1396 are command sponsored and 1685 are 
not the families who are not command sponsored have been urged to 
move to one of the 10 us military installations in panama but 
cannot be forced to do so 
howard said today the flights home were being offered to all 
military dependents in panama including those who were not 
officially sponsored by the military and had decided on their 
own to live there with a husband or wife 
howard said the administration wanted to launch its drawdown 
because of the difficulty of forecasting the actions of the noriega 
government gen manuel antonio noriega the strongman behind that 
government staged and then declared void a popular presidential 
election a week ago when it became clear his candidate had lost 
president bush subsequently ordered almost 2000 additional 
troops to panama to ensure the safety of american citizens 
