consent she said she could not approach her parents for permission 
without fearing emotional or physical abuse 
two days later circuit judge jerry t lockett denied the girls 
petition saying the states abortionconsent law was unworkable 
because it is unconstitutionally vague and does not let judges hold 
proper hearings 
