civil liberties union filed a friendofthecourt brief monday 
claiming that the girl had a constitutional right to privacy and 
hence to an abortion without outside consent 
the florida attorney generals office filed a motion supporting 
the parentalconsent law 
of approximately 75000 abortions performed in florida last 
year about a third were on minors according to prochoice 
activists yet since the new law took effect in february few 
teenagers have gone through the court system to seek a judges 
permission for an abortion 
