<TEXT>
the discovery channel jumped into the 
burgeoning classroom cable television market tuesday with 
assignment discovery a daily teaching aid that boasts no 
commercials and broad support from educators 
the hourlong program due to debut sept 18 will be shown five 
days a week at 9 am eastrn time on cable systems offering the 
discovery channel 
teachers will be allowed to tape the programs and use them as 
needed for up to a year after the initial broadcast 
corporations and foundations will be recruited as underwriters 
discovery officials said but billboards identifying the 
underwriters will not interrupt the two major educational segments 
planned for each hour 
were approaching this first and foremost as a public 
service said discovery chairman john hendricks he said 
satellite time will cost about 250000 a year but declined to 
estimate the price tag on the entire project we dont expect to 
incur huge losses he said 
the fouryearold discovery channel which specializes in 
documentaries is shown on cable systems with 413 million 
subscribers hendricks estimates the channel is already available 
in 65 percent of the nations schools 
the announcement of assignment discovery comes on the heels 
of ted turners announcement that his cable news network will begin 
running a 15minute current events show called cnn newsroom on 
aug 14 teachers will be able to tape the earlymorning program 
and use it in their classrooms 
turner decided at the last minute to nix the commercials 
initially included in the package he said cnn will absorb millions 
of dollars in production costs 
turners entry was widely viewed as competition for a 12minute 
newscast with two minutes of commercials the controversial 
channel one from whittle communications of knoxville tenn the 
program which comes with 50000 in tv equipment for participating 
schools was recently tested in six high schools 
discovery president ruth otte said her network is not in the 
news business and does not consider its new program competition for 
the cnn or whittle shows more power to all of us if we can all 
make a contribution she said 
assignment discovery will feature a particular subject area 
each day of the week science and techology on monday social 
science on tuesday natural science on wednesday arts and 
humanities on thursday and world events and contemporary issues on 
friday 
each hour will consist of two 20to25minute curriculum 
segments an educators bulletin board with news and 
information for teachers and sponsorship billboards between the 
segments the curriculum segments will be drawn from the channels 
extensive documentary collection 
officials said that the program will be aimed at secondary 
school students but that past experience indicates some teachers of 
younger children will also use the programs schools can buy a 
supplemental teaching package for 100 a year and copy it for 
distribution to all interested teachers 
the major obstacle to the series was overcoming copyright 
restrictions hendricks said otte said that educational rights are 
being sought for documentaries already in the networks library and 
that such rights will be included in future contracts with film 
producers 
the series has been developed in consultation with teachers 
administrators and others in the education community a 
characteristic that sets it apart from the whittle and turner 
efforts educators say 
assignment discovery is teacher friendly primarily 
because the discovery channel has taken the time to do its homework 
before jumping into the classroom said lew armistead a 
spokesman for the national association of secondary school 
principals 
this is indeed a partnership said gary marx a spokesman 
for the american association of school administrators he said the 
discovery program is designed primarily to enhance education while 
whittles basic purpose is the commercial exploitation of a 
captive audience of students 
the principals and administrators groups along with the 
national school boards association have formed an advisory panel 
to support the discovery effort 
