<TEXT>
after appearing in the illfated broadway run of 
chess ann crumb is on much firmer ground for her leading role 
in andrew lloyd webbers new megasmash aspects of love 
the eagerly awaited musical opened april 17 at the prince of 
wales theater to an advance sale of 85 million and is sold out 
through 1989 based on a littleknown novel by english writer david 
garnett aspects of love spans 17 years and much of europe 
it casts crumb as rose vibert a volatile french actress 
enmeshed in romantic liaisons involving her husband an expatriate 
painter named george kevin colson his nephew alex michael 
ball and georges italian mistress giulietta kathleen rowe 
mcallen 
