the singing stretches her voice higher than chess and her 
performance has won critical approval with jack tinker in the 
daily mail calling her work vibrantly intelligent and 
commanding 
crumb described the tempestuous rose as a woman who lives on 
the edge all the time 
shes the one who screams and cries and all that crumb 
